=== Dizziness and Vertigo
<subsec:dizziness>

*Clinical Presentation.*

    - Non-spinning dizziness (lightheadedness)
    - True vertigo (sensation of room spinning)
    - Disequilibrium (feeling unsteady)
    - Presyncope (feeling about to faint)
    - Symptoms worsening with position changes, exertion, or sensory stimulation

*Mechanism.*
Dizziness in ME/CFS has multiple contributors: orthostatic intolerance (inadequate cerebral perfusion when upright), vestibular dysfunction, cerebral hypoperfusion, and central processing abnormalities.
